Kasemeni MCA Anthony Yama has asked the more than 500 nursery school teachers hired by the county to campaign for Kwale Governor Salim Mvurya&rsquo;s reelection. &ldquo;Spread the word in your areas,&rdquo; Yama said.Education executive Mangale Chiforomodo said, &ldquo;Mvurya&rsquo;s administration has employed ECDE teachers who previously depended on chicken as fees paid by parents,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;Our ECDE teachers now have pay slips.&rdquo;Kwale Deputy Governor Fatuma Achani urged teachers to support Mvurya as they are the biggest beneficiaries of his administration.